cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel approach to active learning using a generative adversarial network (GAN) for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of a classifier trained with existing labeled data, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which could also place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
